Cell.Text: Where am I? You! Out with it, then.
Ah, I was beginning to think the day would never come. So you broke the binding spell, did you? Matters little. | Their souls are trapped in Oblivion all the same, and here I stay.

Node.Caption: InMiddenBranchTopic: We're beneath Winterhold College. The Midden.

Cell.Text: Where I belong is back aboard my ship, on the Abecean. | You've no hope of defeating me, pup. Don't bother. Why not broker a bargain, instead?

Node.Caption: MiddenThreatenVelehk: You're going back where you belong, Dremora.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Have it your own way, meat.
Those kids are dead anyway. Killing me won't bring them back. I, on the other hand, have done quite a bit with my time on Mundus. | Release me, and I'll share a bit of my wealth with you.

Years back, I had to ferret away some booty nearby. We'd sunk an Imperial Galleon off the coast. Good Plunder, but we needed to travel light. | We stashed what we couldn't carry, and I hid it with a trick I know. I can point you in the right direction, and we'll each go our separate ways.
Names have power, lad. You should know by now. Just say "Velehk Sain, I release you.", and "Poof!", I'm on my way.
Names have power, lass. You should know by now. Just say "Velehk Sain, I release you.", and "Poof!", I'm on my way.

Node.Caption: MiddenHowReleaseVelehk: How could I even release you?

Cell.Text: [S] There's a smart lad. Take the map. The loot's hidden there. It'll show itself when you get near.
[S] There's a smart lass. Check the map. The loot's hidden there. It'll show itself when you get near.
[S] G|See you on the other side, mortal.
[S] G|Clever try, scab, but it won't be that easy!

Node.Caption: MiddenVelehkTrickery: Velehk Sain, I banish you to Oblivion!
